---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

export const prerender = true
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms" description="Terms of service for ilo.">
  <main class="site-frame flex-1 space-y-8 pt-10 pb-12">
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-foreground-muted">Last updated: July 2026</p>
    </section>
    <section class="space-y-6 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Open source software</h2>
        <p>The ilo source code is provided under the MIT license. That license governs your use, copying, modification, and distribution of the software.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Public website and tools</h2>
        <p>ilo.so and its hosted tools are provided as-is and may change, be rate limited, or become unavailable. Do not depend on the public endpoints for critical workloads.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Your accounts and content</h2>
        <p>You are responsible for the accounts you connect, the content you publish, and following the rules and terms of each social network you use.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>Do not use ilo.so to distribute illegal content, spam, malware, or content that infringes another person's rights. Do not abuse or deliberately overload the public tools.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">No warranty</h2>
        <p>Publishing actions can fail, duplicate, or behave differently when a provider changes its API. Review content before confirming publication and keep your own records where they matter.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
